A heavy explosion occurred in the outskirt of Lagos State on Thursday afternoon, throwing residents of the surrounding border communities of Ishaga and Ajunwon into fear of bomb explosion.
Theexplosion engulfed houses in the environment with intense inferno. The cause of the explosion could not be ascertain at the time of this report.
The inferno gradually spread to the surrounding buildings in the environment as two more explosions occurred at the scene.
The emergency communication service in Lagos, however, responded that fire service operatives were on their way to the scene of the incident in the border community of Lagos and Ogun States along Akute road.
